Figure 8 and Figure 9 show simulation results having a super-linear speedup. As the number of processors is
increased, the LP‚Äôs assigned workload decreases, so the sub domain problem complexity is reduced. In general terms,
if we have N individuals to simulate on a serial environment, every individual needs to evaluate the spatial-temporal
position of N ‚àí 1 individuals. In the other case, if we simulate N individuals using P processors, each LP simulates
a NP average of individuals, evaluating only the relative position of NP ‚àí 1 individuals. However, Figure 8 shows the
enhanced model scaling better than the basic model. This shows that increasing the model‚Äôs complexity can help
obtaining a scalability closest to the ideal and more realistic simulation results.
